# Fluxa

## Borderless Banking Powered by Stellar

## Overview

Fluxa is a Stellar-native cross-border treasury and payment platform built for African businesses.
We enable businesses across Africa to receive, hold, convert, and send money globally using modern payment infrastructure powered by the Stellar network.
By combining traditional financial rails with USDC on Stellar, Fluxa provides fast, low-cost, and transparent international payments while maintaining a simple business banking experience.
Businesses can:
Receive international payments
Hold multi-currency balances
Access USD-denominated treasury services
Convert USDC into local African currencies
Pay suppliers, employees, and contractors globally
Manage business finances from a single dashboard
Our mission is simple:
Make global financial access available to every African business through Stellar-powered infrastructure.

## Why Stellar

Current cross-border payments in Africa are slow, expensive, and fragmented.
Traditional international transfers often involve:
Multiple intermediary banks
High transaction fees
Settlement delays
Limited transparency
Fluxa uses the Stellar network as its primary settlement layer.
This enables:
Fast Settlement
Transactions settle within seconds instead of days.
Lower Costs
Businesses avoid many of the fees associated with traditional correspondent banking systems.
Global Reach
Businesses can send and receive value globally using USDC on Stellar.
Transparent Infrastructure
All settlements are traceable and verifiable.
Financial Inclusion
Businesses gain access to global financial tools regardless of local banking limitations.

## The Problem

African businesses face significant barriers when participating in the global economy.
Common challenges include:

### Expensive International Payments

Cross-border transactions remain costly and inefficient.

### Limited Access to Dollar-Based Services

Businesses frequently require access to USD for trade, software subscriptions, and international operations.

### Fragmented Financial Systems

Companies often use multiple providers for:
Payments
Foreign exchange
Treasury management
Invoicing
International transfers

### Currency Risk

Businesses operating in local currencies face volatility that impacts planning and growth.

## Our Solution

Fluxa combines Stellar-powered stablecoin settlement with local financial infrastructure.
Businesses can:
Receive USDC on Stellar
Customers anywhere in the world can pay businesses directly using USDC.
Hold Digital Dollar Balances
Businesses can store treasury funds in USDC while maintaining local currency accounts.
Convert USDC into Local Currency
Supported payout corridors include:
NGN
KES
GHS
ZAR

## Send Global Payments

Businesses can pay:
Suppliers
Freelancers
Contractors
Remote employees
using Stellar-based settlement.
Manage Treasury
Businesses gain access to real-time treasury visibility across all balances and currencies.

## How Fluxa Works

Example Scenario
A software agency in Lagos provides services to a client in the United States.
Step 1
The client sends 5,000 USDC.
Step 2
The payment settles on Stellar within seconds.
Step 3
Fluxa credits the agency treasury account.
Step 4
The agency chooses to:
Hold USDC
Convert to NGN
Pay contractors
Fund business operations
Step 5
Local payouts are executed through regulated financial partners.
The result:
Faster settlements
Lower fees
Better treasury management
Improved cash flow

